Boot-splash custom image and byline for Prusa-Firmware-Buddy
============================================================

Draws a compiled-in image over the bootloader's Prusa logo on the firmware
boot splash and adds a byline beneath the version text. CoreOne family only
(COREONE incl. INDX variants; 480x320 display); other printers compile the
feature out entirely.

This patch is code-only. After applying, the build requires an image at
    src/gui/res/splash/splash_image.png
and reads the byline text from
    src/gui/splash_byline.hpp
The apply script handles both (defaults: the kit's pony, "by @erikbuild"):
    patches/boot-splash/apply.sh [--image your.png] [--text "by @you"] [--version "X.Y.Z+N"]
Manual equivalent:
    git apply patches/boot-splash/boot-splash.patch
    mkdir -p src/gui/res/splash
    cp patches/boot-splash/spedpony_256x152.png src/gui/res/splash/splash_image.png

Image constraints: PNG, at most 480 wide and 157 tall (a static_assert
enforces it must clear the progress bar), transparency flattened on black.
The build converts it to QOI and embeds it in the firmware binary (no
external flash dependency), regenerating whenever the PNG changes. Python
deps (pillow, qoi, numpy) are stock requirements.txt entries.

Version: --version writes "X.Y.Z+N" to version.txt; the patch makes the
build honor the +N as BUILD_NUMBER (explicit -D BUILD_NUMBER= still wins,
and a version.txt without +N keeps stock git-count behavior). Pick N above
the installed firmware's build number so the bootloader auto-offers the
.bbf.

Validate (host unit tests, needs GCC -- see macos-host-unit-tests.patch on
macOS):
    python3 utils/build_tests.py memory_byte_reader_tests -t -- -R MemoryByteReader

Prepared against release 6.6.2. If a future release rejects hunks, the new
files (src/common/memory_byte_reader.hpp, src/gui/splash_byline.hpp,
utils/qoi_to_cpp.py, tests/unit/common/memory_byte_reader_test.cpp) always
apply; only the context edits (cmake/ProjectVersion.cmake,
src/gui/CMakeLists.txt, screen_splash.cpp, screen_splash.hpp,
tests/unit/common/CMakeLists.txt) may need manual replay.

